    {
        "content": "<p>AFAIK some theorems have multiple aliases to allow for more dot notation like you want, but most theorems just choose one of the arguments that makes the most sense to use for dot notation.<br>\nIf you're suggesting adding <code>alias Walk.length_lt_of_isPath := Walk.IsPath.length_lt</code> then I'm for it, but if we're only keeping a single alias then I prefer the current <code>IsPath</code> version.</p>",
        "id": 556968052,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1763433902
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think I also slightly prefer the current <code>IsPath</code> API pattern with the <code>Walk</code> argument typically implicit. </p>\n<p>Even when you don't have  the correct <code>IsPath</code> assumption in context the current version can still be very handy, e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsPath</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">support</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">takeUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">length</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">card</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">takeUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">length_lt</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 558282574,
        "sender_full_name": "John Talbot",
        "timestamp": 1763579071
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"506168\">John Talbot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/252551-graph-theory/topic/Duplicate.20IsPath.20API.20with.20explicit.20Walk.20argument.3F/near/558282574\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think I also slightly prefer the current <code>IsPath</code> API pattern with the <code>Walk</code> argument typically implicit. </p>\n<p>Even when you don't have  the correct <code>IsPath</code> assumption in context the current version can still be very handy, e.g.</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsPath</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">support</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">takeUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">length</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">card</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">takeUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">length_lt</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If, instead of <code>by assumption</code> we use more advanced tactic (based on <code>grind</code> or <code>simp</code> maybe?), then this could be written as:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsPath</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">support</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">takeUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">length</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">card</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">takeUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">length_lt_of_isPath</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So, not much change. But with let binding you could have avoided writing <code>.takeUntil</code> twice.</p>",
        "id": 558514528,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakub Nowak",
        "timestamp": 1763667678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I think, we should strive to automate <code>IsPath</code>. Like automation of array bound checks e.g. So then, you actually don't have to prove it (manually) at all in many simple cases.</p>",
        "id": 558515291,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakub Nowak",
        "timestamp": 1763667970
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Perhaps, but just swapping <code>assumption</code> for <code>grind / simp / aesop</code> will currently fail in this example.</p>\n<p>Also in most simple cases the corresponding lemma (like <code>IsPath.takeUntil</code>) should exist so perhaps adding missing lemmas of this form could help avoid the original problem?</p>",
        "id": 558530576,
        "sender_full_name": "John Talbot",
        "timestamp": 1763673429
    }
]